title: The Offspring Project
name: The Offspring Project
description:
A Map by Jason

Being a parent is a bit like being a mad scientist, at least that's what my dad always said.  

These are some of my parental experiments, and a few cute things just thrown in for fun.

properties.name: 2nd annual candy house deposit
properties.description: Posted by Jason400 SW Kingston Ave, Portland, ORhive posted a photo: for the second year, emiko has made a gingerbread house, and after it\'s time is up, we set it free in the wild somewhere and photograph it

properties.name: Aztec version of a group Sweet 16 Party
properties.description: Posted by Jason   Dolores Park, SF, CACalled something like the Summer Corn Festival, this amazingly energetic and festive gathering drew people of Aztec heritage from all over the Bay Area for the annual celebration of Summer, Corn and mostly the fact that another batch of daughters have turned 15. It was described to us, by one mother of a 15 year old girl, as a version of a sweet 16 party, but for all the girls at once. The conch horns over the simple drumming mixed with incense and incredible feathered costumes made for a very moving and exciting time. Tabor basically tried to be an Aztec drummer the whole rest of the day!

properties.name: Crushed Camera
properties.description: Posted by Jason2347 NW Kearney St, Portland, ORGive a 5 year old your camera, while she is wearing adult size 11 roller skates on bumpy cobblestones and is high on snacks in the summer, and you are asking for trouble. Smashed in lens powershot takes interesting photos. The plan is to gut the parts and remount in an old slr or something . when ever i have some \'project time\'

properties.description: Posted by Deisnor  616 Northwest 21st Avenue, Portland, OR, 97209Jason won the dvd for his costume of chimney sweep and Olivia for her Mary Poppins. All the kids were winners of course. Philly\'s family and ours were clad in our sing along finest. I had misremembered two scenes and ended up wearing a costume of a character which didn\'t exist; white men\'s suit of the safari variety carrying balloons. Hmmm- it matched anyhow. Highly Recommend!

properties.name: Muzzled Dogs and Weak Coffee
properties.description: Posted by Jason  20th & Harrison, SF, CAHad a few minutes to kill before brunch, found a cafe with outdoor seating (the weather was absolutely stunning during the entire trip!) to get some morning coffee. There was a cute gentle occasionally barking dog that got muzzled my her owner during our tenure there, the dog could tell we had pity for her, so she stretched her leash over the sidewalk and lay in the sun close enough to our table that the kids could reach down and pet her. The coffee was amazingly disappointing, i think they don\'t do brewed coffee, so they made us 2 way-too-watery americanos. bummer. The place seemed cool, murals everywhere, and we walked in during a very energetic birthday song being performed by the entire staff (including apron donned cooks).

properties.name: Peeling paper from trees
properties.description: Posted by Jason  jamison square park, nw johnson & 11th, portland, orThe kids will spend at least 20 minutes peeling every shred of loose papery bark from these birch trees every time we come here. It\'s great, except that the trees are surrounded by little gardens of clumsy large-ish stones, that kids just seem to constantly stumble over, so instead of being able to enjoy those rare moments when the kids are absorbed in something, it becomes a constant game of \'pick me up, i fell on these rocks\'. Oh yeah, they also just constantly want to keep all the little \'paper\' scraps in MY pockets. Great.

properties.name: Took Tabor, for a little guy time, to the waterzoo
properties.description: Posted by Jason2820 Se Ferry Slip Rd, Newport, ORHe LOVED IT! we looked at every single exhibit, indoors and out. We were expecting to pet an octopus or something, but weren\'t disappointed with the wide variety of stuff we could actually \'pet\'. Highlights: *the glass tunnels *seeing the scuba guys cleaning the glass of the glass tunnels! *the jellyfish column *the shark jaw posed photo (he was stoked that we could ask other people to take our picture) *the sealions swimming right ot him everytime at the window *petting the starfish *sneaking through the small caves that lead to some outdoor exhibits

properties.name: Took the offspring to the huge public pillow fight
properties.description: Posted by Jason  715 SW Morrison, Portland, OR, 97205Part of a movement, cacophonic, fun, innocent, pure. i had emiko on my shoulders right in the middle of the pit, spinning around, she\'s just hold out her pillow and thwap people\'s heads, her and tabor could not get enough of it. tabor wanted to be on the ground, walking up to peoples\' backs and thwacking them by stealth mode.
